data.title: Wikipedia
data.text:
"Faruq" redirects here. For the village in Iran, see Faruq, Iran.

For the American pro wrestler, see Faarooq. For Al-Farooq, also spelled Al Farouk or Al-Faruq, see Al-Farooq. For the similar Iranian and South Asian given name Farokh, Farrokh, Farukh, Faruque or Farrukh, see Farrokh (name).

Farooq

فاروقPronunciationLiterary Arabic: [fɑːˈruːq, faːˈruːq, fæːˈruːq]

Egyptian Arabic: [fɑˈɾuːʔ]

Levantine Arabic: [faːˈruːʔ]

Persian: [fɒːˈɾuːɣ]

GenderMaleOriginLanguage(s)ArabicMeaningThe one who distinguishes between right and wrong

Farooq (also transliterated as Farouk, Faruqi, Farook, Faruk, Faroeq, Faruq, or Farouq, Farooqi, Faruque or Farooqui; Arabic: فاروق, romanized: Fārūq) is a common Arabic given and family name. Al-Fārūq literally means "the one who distinguishes between right and wrong."
